Chinese restaurant in the busy Tsim Sha Tsui area. Good views. Strangely shaped interior means you have a row of tables. Lots of private rooms available too.

A mix of traditional and modern takes on Chinese food. Truffle on prawns make an interesting combination that I'm not sure if it would fit within Chinese cuisine if not for the vinegar provided. Good quality food overall.
Service and food is good. Worth for a try.

reviews.text: Good location,  good service ,  and reasonable price
他的蝦球強力推薦必點，上海湯包也是強力推薦，但他的蟹膏甚麼的，就是有餅皮去包那個膏這道千萬不要點，我們三個人都覺得貴又不好吃，那個割包夾肉那一道也別點，不好吃。螞蟻上樹沒有台灣口味以及廣東口味的來的好吃，這一道也不建議。碧螺春倒是還不錯這茶。
現在可能比上海的好吃了
